  "culturalNotes": {
    "title": "Indonesian Social Culture 🇮🇩",
    "points": [
      "**Santai culture**: Indonesians value relaxed, unhurried time with friends - known as 'santai-santai' or 'nongkrong' (hanging out).",
      "**Coffee culture**: Cafes (warung kopi) are social hubs where people chat for hours. 'Ngopi' (having coffee) is a social activity, not just drinking coffee!",
      "**Greetings**: 'Apa kabar?' (How are you?) is the standard greeting. The typical response is 'Baik' (Good) or 'Bagus' (Great).",
      "**Friendliness**: Indonesian hospitality is legendary - strangers will often greet you with smiles and help without being asked.",
      "**Music scene**: The Indonesian indie music scene is vibrant, especially in Jakarta, with many local bands and festivals."
    ]
  },

